# Game source boundary

All **game behavior** changes belong in:

- `source/scenes/**/*.scene.dry`
- `source/qdisplays/*.qdisplay.dry`
- `source/info.dry` (title / author metadata only)

**Do not edit `source/lib/*.js` for gameplay.** Those files are dev/CLI mirrors or stale reference copies. The browser build compiles only `.dry` scenes into `out/html/core.js`. If you change logic in a `.js` lib without updating the matching runtime scene, the live game will not change.

| Playable source (edit here) | Dev mirror (sync manually if CLI tests need it) |
|-----------------------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| `election_runtime.scene.dry` | `election-v2.js`, `election-world-data.js` (populations only) |
| `electorate_runtime.scene.dry` | — |
| `economic_assets_runtime.scene.dry` | `economic-asset-name-catalog.js` (reference only) |
| `cards/local_organizing/organize_phase_tick.scene.dry` | — |

After editing a runtime scene, run `npm run make-html`. Use `npm run simulate-election:v2 -- --from-scene` to test election logic extracted from `election_runtime.scene.dry`, not from `election-v2.js` alone.

The **sole source injection** at build time is `scripts/write-build-stamp.js`, which rewrites `Q.build_time_label` in `root.scene.dry` before compile.

## Build output (`out/`)

`npm run make-html` may write all of `out/` through **normal dendrynexus `make-html` behavior** (compile → `core.js`, template copy, etc.). Do not hand-edit `out/` for game logic.

No custom build injections beyond dendrynexus + stamp:

- No project `templates/` overrides
- No post-build patches to `out/html/` for runtime behavior
- No sidecar loaders (e.g. synchronous `game.json` XHR in `index.html`)

### Frozen HTML shell (May 2026 freeze point)

These files match the live deploy at https://araminty.github.io/mikasa/ and are **preserved** across `make-html` (dendrynexus skips overwrite when they already exist):

- `out/html/index.html` — Library link, tabbed sidebar, options (dark mode, etc.)
- `out/html/game.js` — `showStats` → `library`, Mikasa UI hooks
- `out/html/game.css` — Mikasa theme (CSS variables, dark mode, tabs/cards/tooltips)

Do not replace them with stock `default-tabbed-sidebar` output. After `make-html`, only `core.js` (and compiled game data) should change unless you intentionally update the shell.

Dev-only scripts (`lint:dendry`, `simulate-election`, `serve:dev`, `extract-scene-js`) must not affect the playable build.

## Revert test

If every file outside `source/` were reverted to the pre-refactor baseline and you ran `make-html`, in-game behavior should match what the current scene/qdisplay sources describe. Dev tooling may break; that is acceptable.

## Runtime JS pattern

Large JS blocks go in silent setup scenes (`max-visits: 1`, `new-page: false`) with `MIKASA_*_BEGIN` / `END` markers for Node extraction. Bootstrap via `go-to:` from `root.scene.dry`.
